         done
      endif

~ Set up our spell resistance
      var damage as number
      damage = minimum(herofield[tHitDice].value + 5, 30)
      #applysr[damage]]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fCrafAbGly" name="Craft Aboleth Glyph" description="An aboleth with this feat can create magic glyphs that store spells or have specialized effects of their own.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, caster level 5th.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The creature can create a permanent {i}glyph of warding{/i} effect that automatically recharges and replenishes its own energy after a short period of inactivity after it is triggered. Crafting an aboleth glyph takes one day for each 1,000 gp in its base price. The base price of an aboleth glyph is its caster level &#215; spell level &#215; 1,000 gp. To create the glyph, the creature must spend 1/25 of the base price in XP and use up raw materials costing one-half of the base price.\n\nA newly created glyph functions exactly as if the creature had cast {i}glyph of warding{/i} on the affected area, except that the glyph automatically reappears 1 minute after it is discharged. Similarly, if the glyph is dispelled, it reforms as good as new 1 minute later. An aboleth glyph can be destroyed only in the same manner that a magic item can be destroyed&#151;{i}Mordenkainen&#146;s disjunction{/i}, physical destruction of the glyph, and so on.\n\nAlternatively, the aboleth can create a master glyph. Each master glyph is a unique glyph with specific effects and base costs; several sample master glyphs are detailed later in this chapter." compset="Feat" summary="Create permanent {i}glyphs of warding{/i} that recharge themselves." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" parent="p35" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="ItemCreate"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Caster level 5th required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Caster] >= 5]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDeaFrenzy" name="Death Frenzy" description="When an aboleth takes this feat, its sense of immortality rebels against the very concept of death. If threatened with death, the creature becomes frenzied with speed and fury.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Diehard, Endurance.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: If the aboleth is reduced to fewer hit points than its total Hit Dice, it automatically enters a death frenzy. Entering this state is an immediate action; the aboleth can enter a death frenzy even when it&#146;s not its turn. While in a death frenzy, the aboleth cannot cast spells, use spell-like abilities, or use supernatural special attacks.\n\nWhen an aboleth enters a death frenzy, it gains a +4 morale bonus to its Strength and Dexterity, and the threat range for all its natural attacks doubles. When it makes a full attack, it can make one additional attack each round at its highest base attack bonus. Its land speed increases by 10 feet, and its swim speed increases by 20 feet. Finally, it gains fast healing 2.\n\nA death frenzy lasts until the creature is killed or until its hit points rise enough to equal or exceed its total number of Hit Dice. Upon emerging from a death frenzy, the creature immediately takes 1d4 points of Strength damage." compset="Feat" summary="Imm, if Hp &lt; HD +4 Str &amp; Dex, dbl threat, extra att, +10/20 spd, fast heal 2." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Diehard required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fDiehard] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Endurance required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fEndure] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fEnlMuClo" name="Enlarge Mucus Cloud" description="An aboleth with this feat can extend its mucus cloud into a wider area.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Con 20.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The aboleth&#146;s mucus cloud extends to fill an area equal to its natural reach (a 10-foot radius for most aboleths).\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: The aboleth&#146;s mucus cloud has a radius of only 1 foot.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: On land, the aboleth&#146;s mucus cloud becomes a mucus puddle of an equal radius. The mucus can affect other beings in contact with the puddle (including any that move through it using their base land speed), but beings that jump or fly over it, or otherwise avoid the puddle, are safe." compset="Feat" summary="Mucus cloud increases to reach, forms puddle on land of equal radius." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 20 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 20]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMemoEater" name="Memory Eater" description="An aboleth with this feat is particularly adept at extracting memories and knowledge from the bodies of those it consumes.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Cha 21.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The aboleth processes and remembers countless memories of those it has eaten. It can make untrained skill checks in any skill, including those in which it has no ranks and that normally cannot be used untrained.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Aboleths receive only random flashes of memory that quickly fade while eating the flesh of an intelligent creature." compset="Feat" summary="Retain memories of those eaten &amp; make untrained checks for train only skills." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)

Eval (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <eval phase="First"><![CDATA[    var result as number
  foreach pick in hero from BaseSkill where "Helper.TrainOnly"
   perform each.delete[Helper.TrainOnly]
  nexteach]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 21 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 21]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAbPowBite" name="Powerful Bite" description="An aboleth with this feat develops jaws that are much more muscular than normal, allowing it to bite more efficiently.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Str 28, Weapon Focus (bite).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: An aboleth with this feat gains a natural bite attack that deals 2d6 points of damage plus half its Strength modifier. If the aboleth makes a full attack, this bite attack is a secondary attack and is made with a &#150;5 penalty on the attack roll.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: The aboleth&#146;s bite attack is an unarmed strike that takes a full round action to use and deals 1d4 points of damage on a hit." compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)

Eval (Done)

Test? (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xAbPowBite"></bootstrap>
    <exprreq message="Strength 28 required."><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 28]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Weapon Focus (bite) required."><![CDATA[tagis[WepFocus.wBite] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fQuickslim" name="Quickslime" description="The slime attack of an aboleth with this feat is particularly fast and difficult to resist.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Ability Focus (slime).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The save DC of the creature&#146;s slime attack gains a +2 bonus; this stacks with the bonus granted by the Ability Focus (slime) feat. Further, the transformation process takes only 1d4+1 rounds to affect the victim&#146;s skin.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: The transformation process takes 1d4+1 minutes." compset="Feat" summary="+2 DC for slime and skin transforms in 1d4+1 rds." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Ability Focus (slime) required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAbilFoc] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fReachBite" name="Reach Bite" description="An aboleth with this feat can extend its jaws and esophagus out from its body to make attacks beyond its normal reach.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Str 28, Powerful Bite, Weapon Focus (bite).\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The creature&#146;s reach with its bite attack extends by an additional 5 feet.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: The creature&#146;s bite attack has a reach equal to its standard reach (10 feet for most aboleths)." compset="Feat" summary="+5 ft reach for bite attack." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Strength 28 required."><![CDATA[child[aSTR].field[aFinalVal].value >= 28]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Powerful Bite required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAbPowBite] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Weapon Focus (bite) required."><![CDATA[tagis[WepFocus.wBite] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fThickMucu" name="Thicken Mucus" description="An aboleth with this feat can produce mucus that is thicker than normal, and other creatures find it difficult to swim through.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Con 22, Enlarge Mucus Cloud.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Creatures within range of the mucus cloud have their swim speed reduced by half if they start their movement in the cloud. Additionally, all creatures in melee with this aboleth take a &#150;1 penalty on attack rolls, Armor Class, and Reflex saving throws.\n\nAboleths, skum, and creatures transformed by an aboleth&#146;s slime attack are unaffected by Thicken Mucus and can move through the cloud without penalty.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: When on land, this ability affects only non aboleth (or non transformed creatures) that walk through the mucus puddle. The land speed of these creatures is reduced by half, and their swim speed is not affected. Flying creatures are not affected.\n\n{i}Freedom of movement{/i} negates these penalties." compset="Feat" summary="Foe in mucus cloud swim &#189; spd, in melee take -1 attack, AC &amp; Ref saves." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 22 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 22]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Enlarge Mucus Cloud required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fEnlMuClo] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fToxicMucu" name="Toxic Mucus" description="An aboleth with this feat can produce mucus that is poisonous to other creatures.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aboleth, Con 22, Enlarge Mucus Cloud, Thicken Mucus.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Any creature that comes in contact with the mucus cloud becomes poisoned. The creature must make a successful Fortitude save (DC 10 + half the aboleth&#146;s Hit Dice + Con modifier) or take 1d4 points of Dexterity damage. One minute later, the creature must save again against the same DC or take another 1d4 points of Dexterity damage. Creatures that remain in the mucus cloud for multiple rounds must make additional saving throws each round.\n\nAboleths, skum, and creatures transformed by an aboleth&#146;s slime attack are immune to the effect of Toxic Mucus and can move through the cloud without penalty.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: When on land, this ability affects only non aboleth (or non transformed creatures) that walk through the mucus puddle; flying creatures are not affected.\n\nAn aboleth must replenish its mucus constantly to maintain the poisonous qualities. Samples taken from the aboleth retain their toxic qualities for only 1 minute." compset="Feat" summary="Mucus is poisonous, does 1d4 Dex/1d4 Dex (DCXX Fort neg)." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)

xSumm (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostAt" priority="10000"><![CDATA[      var DC as number
      DC = 10 + herofield[tHitDice].value/2 + hero.child[aCON].field[aModBonus].value 
      DC = round(DC, 0, -1)

      field[xSumm].text = "Mucus is poisonous, does 1d4 Dex/1d4 Dex (DC" & DC & " Fort neg)."]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Constitution 22 required."><![CDATA[child[aCON].field[aFinalVal].value >= 22]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Enlarge Mucus Cloud required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fEnlMuClo] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Thicken Mucus required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fThickMucu] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Aboleth race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Aboleth] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAgiTyrant" name="Agile Tyrant" description="A creature with this feat develops longer, more flexible eyestalks than its kin. This extra flexibility allows it to bring additional eye rays to bear against its foes.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: True beholder or beholderkin.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The creature can direct an extra eye ray into a single 90-degree arc." compset="Feat" summary="Can direct an extra eye ray into each 90 degree arc." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="True beholder or beholderkin race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Beholder] + hero.tagis[Race.Beholdrkin] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBaneUncle" name="Bane of the Unclean" description="A creature with this feat hates aberrant beholders so strongly that it gains bonuses when fighting them.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: True beholder or must have aberration as a favored enemy.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The creature gains a +2 morale bonus on attack rolls, weapon damage rolls, touch Armor Class, and saving throws when fighting a beholderkin.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If the creature is a true beholder, the benefits of this feat apply to other true beholders as well as to beholderkin." compset="Feat" summary="+2 morale bon to att, weap dam, touch AC &amp; saves vs beholderkin." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="True beholder or Favored Enemy: Aberration required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Beholder] + childfound[feAberr].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDisintFin" name="Disintigration Finesse" description="A creature with this feat can use disintegrate effects to affect smaller, more exacting areas.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Dex 13, ability to cast {i}disintegrate{/i} as a spell or use it as a spell-like or supernatural ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When the creature uses disintegrate on a target, it can elect to disintegrate only portions of the target. Against living targets, it still does the normal amount of damage, but any parts of the target it wishes to spare remain unaffected by the spell. The creature could, for example, disintegrate only a target&#146;s skeleton, leaving its skull untouched. It also can voluntarily reduce the amount of damage dealt.\n\nAgainst non living targets, the creature can use disintegrate to sculpt and reshape the object in any manner desired, as long as the result is no larger in volume or size than the original object. The quality of the result is determined by a Craft (sculpting) check.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: A disintegrate effect destroys all of a slain creature, an entire object, or one 10-foot cube of nonliving matter.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: If your campaign uses the Damage to Specific Areas variant rule on page 27 of the Dungeon Master&#146;s Guide, a creature with this feat can disintegrate a single part of a target&#146;s body, such as its hand, arm, head, eyes, ears, feet, legs, and so on, as long as the target is not killed outright by the damage caused by the spell." compset="Feat" summary="May disintigrate only part of foe, reduce dam, or sculpt unliving material." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Dexterity 13 required."><![CDATA[child[aDEX].field[aFinalVal].value >= 13]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDisjunRay" name="Disjunction Ray" description="A beholder with this feat can narrow its antimagic cone down to an eye ray that disjoins magic.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Cha 19, Focused Antimagic, beholder with functional antimagic ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, the creature can reduce the cone-shaped area of effect of its central eye&#146;s antimagic cone down to a razor-thin eye ray. If the creature hits a magical effect or magic item with this narrowed eye ray, it disjoins the effect or item as if it had cast {i}Mordenkainen&#146;s disjunction{/i} on the effect or item.\n\nBeholders avoid using this narrowed ray on magic items since the destruction of a magic item also destroys a potential source of magic that could be used to charge their dweomerlobes." compset="Feat" summary="Stand, narrow antimagic cone to thin ray to disjoin an item or effect." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Charisma 19 required."><![CDATA[child[aCHA].field[aFinalVal].value >= 19]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Focused Antimagic required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fFocAntMag] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Beholder with functional central eye required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Beholder] - hero.tagis[User.NoCentrEye] > 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fFocAntMag" name="Focused Antimagic" description="A beholder with this feat can focus the antimagic of its central eye to target a single person or object.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Beholder with functional antimagic ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: The creature can reduce the cone-shaped area of effect of its central eye to target a single creature or object. The target must be within range of its normal cone-shaped effect (150 feet)." compset="Feat" summary="Can narrow antimagic cone to affect only a single creature/item." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="Beholder with functional central eye required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Beholder] - hero.tagis[User.NoCentrEye] > 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fMetaray" name="Metaray" description="A beholder with this feat can apply the effects of metamagic feats to its eye rays.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: True beholder or beholderkin, at least one metamagic feat.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Once per round, as a standard action, the creature can enhance one of its eye rays with the effect of a metamagic feat that it possesses. Enhancing an eye ray in this manner burns the eyestalk out for a number of rounds equal to the amount by which the metamagic would normally increase a spell level. Since firing an eye ray that hasn&#146;t been enhanced with metamagic is a free action, the creature still can use its other eye rays in a round in which it enhances one ray with metamagic.\n\nFor example, if a beholder had the Maximize Spell feat and the Metaray feat, it could take a standard action to fire a maximized {i}inflict moderate wounds{/i} eye ray that would cause 26 points of damage on a hit. Its {i}inflict moderate wounds{/i} eyestalk would then not be usable for the next 3 rounds.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: The creature cannot use this ability with a metamagic feat that would increase the level of a spell by more than three levels." compset="Feat" summary="1/rd, stand, add known MM to eye ray (max 3 lvl) then dormant for lvl rds." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message="True beholder or beholderkin race required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Race.Beholder] + hero.tagis[Race.Beholdrkin] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Any metamagic feat required."><![CDATA[hero.tagcount[fCategory.Metamagic] >= 1]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fSkilTelek" name="Skilled Telekinetic" description="A creature with this feat becomes so skilled with its {i}telekinesis{/i} ability that it can manipulate and use magic items via telekinesis.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Ability to use telekinesis as a supernatural ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: As a standard action, the creature can use its telekinetic power to trigger a command word, spell completion, or spell trigger magic item as long as the item is unattended and the creature could normally utilize the item when holding it. The magic item must be within reach of the creature&#146;s {i}telekinesis{/i} ability, the creature must have line of sight with its target, and the creature must have line of effect between the magic item and the target. The item must otherwise fulfill all the requirements for manipulating an object via {i}telekinesis{/i} (such as weight)." compset="Feat" summary="Stand, use unattended command word, spell comp/trigger item via telekinesis." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre-req. (Done)

Only Ghost and Beholder get Telekinesis as Su ability, others Spell like ability (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <exprreq message=" Ability to use telekinesis as a supernatural ability required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[User.SuTelekine] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAberBaMag" name="Aberration Banemagic" description="You can cast spells that do additional damage to aberrations.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you cast a spell that deals damage to an aberration, you deal an extra 2d6 points of damage.\n\nA single spell can never gain this extra damage more than once per casting. For instance, a {i}fireball{/i} deals the extra damage to all aberrations in the area it affects. However, if a 3rd-level wizard casts {i}magic missile{/i} and produces two missiles, only one of them (of the wizard&#146;s choice) gains the extra damage, whether or not both missiles are directed at the same aberration or two different aberrations. If a spell deals damage for more than 1 round, it deals this extra damage in each round.\n\nScrolls scribed by you do not gain any benefit from Aberration Banemagic. Scrolls activated by you also gain no benefit from Aberration Banemagic. The same is true for most other magic items, such as wands and potions. However, staffs activated by you use not only your caster level but also gain the benefit of this feat, if applicable.\n\nIf the spell allows a saving throw, the DC of the saving throw increases by 2. The additional damage dealt by this spell is either halved on a successful saving throw or negated entirely, depending on how the regular damage dealt by the spell is affected by a successful saving throw." compset="Feat" summary="+2 DC and +2d6 spell dam vs aberrations." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>DONE!!!</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xAberrFeat" name="Aberrant Feat Penalties" description="This book adds a new feat type: the aberrant feat. Unlike typical feats, aberrant feats manifest as physical changes to your character&#146;s features (or as additions to your character&#146;s appearance). These feats twist and reshape your form, and you become alien in appearance.\n\nA character who has selected at least one aberrant feat gains an inhuman, unsettling presence. You take a &#150;1 penalty on Diplomacy, Disguise, Gather Information, Handle Animal, and wild empathy checks for every aberrant feat you possess (&#150;2 with two feats, &#150;3 with three feats, and so on).\n\nSome aberrant feats have an additional cumulative effect based on your total number of aberrant feats. This accumulation increases as you gain additional aberrant feats. For example, a character with Aberration Blood who selects Durable Form gains 4 hit points (two for each aberrant feat he possesses). If he later selects Bestial Hide, he gains another 2 hit points (in addition to the normal benefit of Bestial Hide)." compset="Special" uniqueness="unique">
    <comment>Test? (Done)</comment>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="11000">var pen as number
pen = hero.tagcount[fCategory.Aberrant]

#skillbonus[kDiplomacy] -= pen
#skillbonus[kDisguise] -= pen
#skillbonus[kGatherInf] -= pen
#skillbonus[kHandleAnm] -= pen</eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAberWiSha" name="Aberration Wild Shape" description="Most druids detest aberrations and think of them as outside nature, but some view them simply as examples of nature from an extreme and alien world. Thanks to your heritage, you are one of these latter, and have learned to channel your inhuman bloodline into your shapeshifting power.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aberration Blood, wild shape ability.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can use your wild shape ability to assume the form of an aberration. This otherwise functions identically to your normal wild shape ability. The size of the aberration is limited by the size of animal you can normally assume the shape of with wild shape." compset="Feat" summary="Wild shape includes aberration forms as well as animals." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Aberrant"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xAberrFeat"></bootstrap>
    <exprreq message="Aberration Blood required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAberBlood] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Wild Shape required."><![CDATA[hero.tagis[Hero.WildShape] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fAquaSpell" name="Aquatic Spellcasting" description="You know how to cast spells that work equally well in or out of water.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Water does not impede your spells. Creatures partially or completely submerged do not gain cover or total cover when you cast a spell from outside the water. The surface does not block line of effect for any spell, including spells with the fire descriptor. You need not make a Spellcraft check to cast a fire spell underwater.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Partially or completely submerged creatures gain improved or total cover against attacks from land. The water surface blocks line of effect for fire spells. Fire spells do not function underwater unless the caster succeeds on a Spellcraft check (DC 20 + spell level)." compset="Feat" summary="Water never grants cover/blocks line of effect, &amp; no spellcraft chk for fire spells." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fBeastHide" name="Beastial Hide" description="Your skin is thicker, scalier, or furrier than normal.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Aberration Blood.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Your natural armor bonus to AC improves by 1 for every two aberrant feats you possess." compset="Feat" uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)

Eval (Done)

Test? (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Aberrant"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xAberrFeat"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we're disabled, do nothing
      if (tagis[Helper.FtDisable] <> 0) then
        done
        endif

     var aber as number
     aber = round(hero.tagcount[fCategory.Aberrant]/2, 0, -1)

     ~ Bonus to Natural Armor
     hero.child[ArmorClass].field[tACNatural].value += aber]]></eval>
    <exprreq message="Aberration Blood required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fAberBlood] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDarkstalk" name="Darkstalker" description="You have learned how to stalk and surprise creatures whose senses are very different from those of a humanoid.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: When you hide, creatures with blindsense, blindsight, scent, or tremorsense must make a Listen check or a Spot check (whichever DC is higher) to notice you, just as sighted creatures would make Spot checks to detect you. You cannot hide in plain sight unless you have that ability as a class feature. In addition, you can flank creatures that have the all-around vision special quality.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Creatures with these senses do not need to make Spot or Listen checks to notice other creatures within range. Creatures with all-around vision can&#146;t be flanked." compset="Feat" summary="Blindsense/sight, scent, or tremorsense need spot/listen chk to sense." uniqueness="useronce">
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="General"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fDeepspawn" name="Deepspawn" description="The abnormalities of your aberration-tainted heritage grow more pronounced. Your body undergoes a shocking degeneration into something that is strikingly inhuman.\n\n{b}Prerequisites{/b}: Aberration Blood, one other aberrant feat.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: Two short but powerful tentacles sprout from your waist. You gain two tentacle natural attacks that each deal 1d4 points of damage (for a Medium creature) plus your Strength modifier. The tentacle attacks are treated as primary weapons.\n\nYou can attack with weapons and also make tentacle attacks, but your tentacle attacks are treated as secondary weapons: The attacks are made with a &#150;5 penalty on the attack roll, and you add only 1/2 your Strength bonus to the damage roll.\n\nYou gain a +2 racial bonus on grapple checks." compset="Feat" summary="Gain two primary tentacle attacks." uniqueness="useronce">
    <comment>Pre req (Done)

Eval (Done)</comment>
    <usesource source="LordMadnes" name="Lords of Madness"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Aberrant"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xAberrFeat"></bootstrap>
    <bootstrap thing="xDSTentacl"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="First" priority="105000"><![CDATA[
      ~ If we're disabled, do nothing
      if (tagis[Helper.FtDisable] <> 0) then
        done
        endif

